The article is a statement by the President of the United States, expressing his support for the Nobel Committee's decision to award the Nobel Peace Prize to Mr. Liu Xiaobo. The President acknowledges that others who have received the award have sacrificed more than he has, and now Mr. Liu joins that list by sacrificing his freedom for his beliefs. The President commends Mr. Liu for being an eloquent and courageous spokesman for universal values, including democracy, human rights, and the rule of law. The President also highlights the progress China has made in economic reform but emphasizes that political reform has not kept pace, and calls on the Chinese government to release Mr. Liu as soon as possible.